Class ClassifierSimilarityMeasure

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.tudarmstadt.ukp.similarity.algorithms.api.TermSimilarityMeasureBase
      • de.tudarmstadt.ukp.similarity.algorithms.api.TextSimilarityMeasureBase

          • de.tudarmstadt.ukp.similarity.algorithms.ml.ClassifierSimilarityMeasure
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JCasTextSimilarityMeasure, SimilarityMeasure, TermSimilarityMeasure, TextSimilarityMeasure

    public class ClassifierSimilarityMeasure
extends JCasTextSimilarityMeasureBase
    Runs a machine learning classifier on the provided test data on a model that is trained on the given training data. The available classifiers are Naive Bayes, J48, SMO, and Logistic. Mind that the getSimilarity method classifies the input texts by their ID, not their textual contents. The 
    DocumentID
    of the 
    DocumentMetaData
    is expected to denote the corresponding input line in the test data.
